HEADWORD: Fierasfer
<hw>Fi`e*ras"fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small, slender fishes, remarkable for
their habit of living as commensals in other animals. One species
inhabits the gill cavity of the pearl oyster near Panama; another lives
within an East Indian holothurian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fierce</ent>⟦br⟧
